    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen operatin behind a company proxy / firewall, where PyPI cannot be directly reached, the healthcheck fails for the Python 3 Provider.\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/773bdd41ec19c9909e979c4580cf098d71d168d7/runtime/autoload/health/provider.vim#L155-L168\n### Expected behavior\n\nAn alternate healthcheck url (e.g. a private Nexus or PyPi proxy) should be configurable in the provider settings, e.g.:\n`vim.g.python_provider_healthcheck_url = 'some_url_here'`",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> behind a company proxy / firewall, where PyPI cannot be directly reached\n\nWe may need to think about a more general mechanism for proxy support. Especially after https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/23232\n\nAdding random settings for random network calls (such as provider checks) doesn't seem like the right approach.",
