            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> > behind a company proxy / firewall, where PyPI cannot be directly reached\n> \n> We may need to think about a more general mechanism for proxy support. Especially after [#23232](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/23232)\n> \n> Adding random settings for random network calls (such as provider checks) doesn't seem like the right approach.\n\nWhile I do agree with this sentiment, I disagree with your reasoning to some degree.\n\nRight now the version-check URL is hardcoded and non-changeable. The URL is unreachable because of firewall settings and therefore can be considered a semi-broken state. A config option for the current version would be a useable interim solution.\n\nHowever, in support of your statement, using curl to check for the latest version of a pypi package is not the best of tools, since presumably the user has pypi configured with their internal organization's repositories.\n\nIf this call were changed to use pypi to check for a latest version, it would add some complexity (especially with python virtual environments) but would be a more appropriate approach.",
