            "body": "> The URL is unreachable because of firewall settings and therefore can be considered a semi-broken state.\n\nIt's completely fine if a healthcheck is broken in weird environments, until we have a general answer for proxy support.\n\n> If this call were changed to use pypi to check for a latest version,\n\nYeah we should do that. I half-assumed that the URL check was in case Nvim didn't actually have a local `pip` to work with, but that doesn't really make sense to support.\n\n",
